column3: Note: Pursuant to Rule 6A-1.09981, F.A.C, the grading scale for elementary schools is as follows: A=62% of points or greater; B=54% to 61% of points; C=41% to 53% of points; D=32% to 40% of points; and F=31% of points or less. Additionally, the grading scale for middle, high, and combination schools is as follows: A=64% of points or greater; B=57% to 63% of points; C=44% to 56% of points; D=34% to 43% of points; and F=33% of points or less.
